<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Becomes No. 1 Blue Jeans Producer </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Becomes No. 1 Blue Jeans Producer </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0304144494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1356 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0304144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Xiamen, April 3 (XINHUA) -- The delta of southern 
Fujian has become the largest manufacturing center of blue jeans 
in China. 
  From the streets to garment shops, in the post offices and 
on 
goods trains, blue jeans dot the landscape all year round in the 
Xiamen-Quanzhou-Hangzhou delta. 
  The industry took off after blue jeans gained instant 
popularity when they were introduced to the area from Hong Kong 
and Taiwan in the 1980s. 
  The past decade witnessed garment factories "spring up like 
bamboo shoots after spring rain". No-one can tell the exact 
number of these factories and the amount of their production 
except that truck-load upon truck-load of the clothes are being 
transported to other parts of China daily. 
  Many big producers have set up special counters in 
department 
stores in large cities. Some have even made inroads in other 
countries' markets. 
  In the midst of tough competition, manufacturers are 
upgrading equipment and turning out new designs at an 
increasingly faster rate. 
  As a local factory director puts it: "Only when you lead the 
trend can you survive." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

